<TITLE> Police take Kabirul for quizzing after confession </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 21 (bdnews24.com)Police on Thursday remanded Kabirul Islam Bharasa , son of former Jatiya party MP Karim Uddin, for two days for questioning after he made his confessional statement in the court. Magistrate Konika Biswas of the Court of Dhaka Chief Metropolitan Magistrate recorded his statement from noon to evening. In his statement, he said that he developed a feud with his brother over business. Meanwhile he became addicted to various illicit drugs including Yaba, Kabirul said and added that because of the intoxicating effects of drugs, he sometimes lost his sense. According to plan, he collected a pistol and went to his younger brother's office and shot him dead ,he said Police arrested him on Wednesday at a rehabilitation centre for drug addicts in the city's Uttarkhan area.. On Apr 27, Kabirul shot Khairul dead at the latter's Bijojnagar office over business feud b
